caption: Love this restaurant, it's a small location but it's very nice. Good music and amazing food. Definitely my go to brunch spot

It was my first time there. The location is small but not crowded which made me feel safe. The food was seasoned well and delicious. Our waitress was a friendly young woman named Brenda who made good recommendations.

Everything here is so good!! I remember trying this place within my first few days of living in the area (pre-COVID); it was a cold snowy day, didn't want to leave and definitely regretted going out when I was out in the snow. But when I arrived, the regret soon melted away. I'm a huge fan of sopes, believe me this was probably one of the best. The masa was so fresh and perfect crisp/soft consistency. Service was attentive and personable but laidback. This place is very unassuming on the outside and easy to miss, but you'll be glad you tried!
everything made here is so unique and high quality. love this place. do not hesitate or miss out!
SO good and the LOVELIEST people

(Translated by Google) The food is delicious, the service is excellent, I love hot chocolate it tastes delicious.  (Original) La comida es deliciosa, el servicio es excelente, me encantan el chocolate caliente sabe delicioso.

The food here is incredible AND wildly imaginative. The tacos are just as good as the pancakes. The menu is always changing, the service is so good. It’s impossible not to have a good time here. It’s only a matter of time until it will be impossible to get a table here.
Great food, amazing service! I’ll definitely come back for those sopes. Gotta support small businesses!
Amazing, amazing food great service
The place is small but it packs a punch. Great food, great service. Everything was fresh and vibrant packed full of flavor. Definitely the kind of place to visit regularly.
Authentic Mexican flavors with a gourmet twist in a casual setting. Quirky and creative plates. Fresh salsa. Nutty coffee. Staff cares deeply about your experience. Going back tomorrow!

During this tough time ❤️✨ support places you love! Between the staff and the food I don’t know which to praise more, both stellar.  This is my go to breakfast spot. They make a mean cup of coffee, the eggs are always fluffy and just right, thick cut bacon, potatos with crema, and pancakes (I wish it was morning now)! We’ve had their specialty tacos and dishes also super delicious. If their short rib sandwich is on the menu, GET IT!!!!  What makes the food that much more special, is the staff. They are THE nicest people. Maybe it’s the love they put into their food that makes it extra delicious. This place makes food you dream about. Thank you NEWYORKTITLAN 💓
Fantastic

Beautiful people and food!!!! Some of the nicest service I've had. PLEASE go show some support during covid, there are two little outdoor seating tables or you can takeout. I want this place to stay around. We were really impressed. Inventive Mexican dishes with authentic fresh ingredients. Cannot stress how much we enjoyed the experience ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️

Not too big, but not too small, (there are about 6 tables + 3 seats at eth window) this place is somewhat easy to miss. I went there for a late breakfast, and ordered the Mexican hot chocolate and the Huevos Benedictos.  The hot chocolate was good, and they toast the marshmallow at the table, which was cool. The only downside is that between the cup, the amount of hot chocolate, and the whipped cream, there was almost no way for me to easily get the hot chocolate out without spilling a little bit. That then got onto the paper that's between the saucer and the cup, and created an annoying situation where I had to make sure to undue the suction before picking up my cup. Moving on.  The huevos benedictos were great. They make sure to toast the English muffin, which some places neglect to do. Egg was nicely runny. The potatoes and sauces were well done. I was surprised at how full I felt after the meal, and was glad that I hadn't ordered an appetizer or anything else.
Carnitas were great. Nice atmosphere and friendly service.
Great coffee. Very attentive staff. Tip: the french toast
Great food and service!
Incredible caffe con panna with a delicious chilaquiles. Loved the ambiance and the staff was very warm and friendly. Will definitely return the next time I'm in the area.

I came here because the reviews where great. Food was the good the everything freshly made . Our waiter was good very informative with the menu. When it was time to pay I have him $20.00 cash and my card to pay the remaining 4.00$ Balance so he brings the iPad which is now common now how you pay he inserts my card paying the 4$ hands me iPad to sign then looks at it after I signed then says “There’s no tip” “where is the tip” mind you my friend had left cash on the table for the tip so I told him the tip is right there which we had place under a glass cup so the money wouldn’t fly away it was clearly visible. Like seriously? So rude makes me not even wanted to give him a tip at all! NEVER GOING BACK AGAIN!
Service was amazing. Food was so yummy. The location is super small, but worth it.
Great food with amazing service!
(Translated by Google) All very delicious and the service very good.  (Original) Todo muy delicioso y el servicio muy bueno.
Absolutely perfect. Delicious and beautiful food, fantastic service, great prices. I loved the huevos ahogados but I can't wait to try the rest of the menu.

I don’t know why it’s taken me so long to finally have a sit down here! Came in on the later side so we missed out on some specials, but feel lucky to have made it with enough time to be sat down. Our server was thorough with the menu and the specials, very helpful and passionate about what magic is happening behind the kitchen. Props to the chef for maintain authenticity with his food while still being innovative. I’m sure you know by now, but the pancakes. My god the pancakes. Changing periodically, I hope to make it back before this celebration of a dish is gone. Don’t think twice about making you way over, just don’t be late.
OJ and Huevos a la Mexicana was fire, great service!
Most underrated spot in the area. The people who run this joint care so much. The chef is talented and the food shows and tastes amazing.
This is one of the best brunch spots around and is super low key.

The food here is some of the most interesting Mexican I have ever had. Their brunch especially is worth making a date for. It is small inside so perhaps call ahead to make sure to get a table. Try the daily pancakes, they are to die for!

So so good. I got eggs benedict and asked for a salmon substitution, which they happily approved. Hollandaise was awesome, eggs and bread were great, potatoes on the side were awesome, and service was so efficient and pleasant. Would definitely come back and recommend to anyone!!!
This is my new favorite spot around... refined Mexican brunch and breakfast. The huevos benedictos is one of the most unique eggs benedicts in the city, and one of the most delicious.
Cozy little place, a little pricey but the service was nice and very quick and the food was amazing. Great healthy options and good coffee

A small and cozy neighborhood restaurant with delicious breakfast options. The eggs Benedict were super delicious, the hollandaise sauce was just right with a little bit of lime. Waitress was very friendly and attentive, she also offered us complementary little pancakes with banana purée which melted in my mouth! Highly recommend to stop by for breakfast if you’re in the area.
Everything here is delicious
Don't let the size of this place fool you. It's small, but packed with flavor. Food tastes amazing here.
It’s my third time here, I tried different plates, and its all good. Great neighborhood restaurant, very good service. Will always come back!
Deliciously FANCY!!! Love it!!! Best breakfast recipes. A+ Avocado Truffle is a must try...
Just finished a great meal in the NewMexican restaurant. Never heard of this place just found it on yelp, but it was a great surprise the food was amazing. Very nice staff as well.
Excellent service and food. Super attentive staff!!!! Should definitely check out if you’re in bushwick!
Great tdaition latinx food with a modern twist
Perfect every time.
Excelent find. Best brunch I've had in years. The coffee is incredible, the food is extraordinary and done with care. The service is great and the atmosphere is very cool. Good job guys

I've been here twice. The service and food have been really great both times. The poblano crema on their homefries is amazing. The moyete and Mexican hot chocolate are so delicious. The salsa verde is so so good.The only issue I have is that their hours are a bit erratic.

This is a must-try place! Food is delicious, staff are more than friendly and accommodating. They're even giving to their own community, because when I went they were donating all proceeds that day to a friend in need of an operation. So they made "special" pancakes.  I hope this place continues to do well, their chef knows what he is doing!
